data.name: LabelUSERtab1.Text
data.value:
The WinGPIB User tab allows you to:
- Load a simple text-based configuration file to build a complete custom control panel — no recompiling required - Keep multiple configuration files, each tailored to a specific instrument, test setup, or measurement task, and switch between them as needed - Create buttons, textboxes, charts, stats panels, LEDs, dropdowns, and more dynamically at runtime - Bind controls directly to GPIB / SCPI commands for any connected instrument (dev1, dev2) - Execute scripted lists of GPIB/SCPI commands with optional periodic execution and automatic logging to file - Run auto-refresh measurements, live charts, statistics, and history logging - Define trigger logic and chained actions without writing application code - Execute Lua scripts for advanced sequencing, automation, and multi-instrument control - Control existing buttons and functions elsewhere in WinGPIB from LUA scripts - Build repeatable test, calibration, and data-logging workflows using plain text files
In short: The User tab lets you turn WinGPIB into a custom instrument front panel and automation system, tailored exactly to your setup.
Note: User area size = 1030 × 547 Coordinate origin (0,0) is at the top-left corner

data.name: Label227.Text
data.value: Connect to device and leave in STOP position. Select Query or Send Async prior to sending command. Type command and press ENTER to send. Internal cmd's: #QA = Set to Query Async mode #SA = Set to Send Async mode

data.name: Label243.Text
data.value:
1. Select 'Send.....' radio button. 2. Select the sections you wish to upload. 3. Select the JSON file with the data you want to upload. 4. Hit the 'Upload to Ram' button to upload the data to your R6581(T). 5. Test your R6581(T) and if all is good then hit the 'Commit Ram to EEprom' button to transfer the contents permanently to EEprom.
If your test does not work out for you then reset your R6581(T), the ram upload will be abandoned and the EEprom data will remain unchanged.

data.name: Label245.Text
data.value:
Regular calibration data management: Read/write cal constants from/to Ram. Reading previous cal data from EEProm. Eprom update command to write Ram to EEprom.
Factory calibration data management: Used during the initial setup of the instrument to eliminate small errors/artifacts. Split into DCV && AC.
Retrieve 7.2Vdc && 10kohm reference value drift history.
Previous (old) calibration constants are not extracted.

data.name: Label267.Text
data.value:
3245A Security code only req'd if hardware lockout jumper is in place.
The 3458A/344xxA/R6581(T) DMM is set up automatically.
Channel A or B on the 3245A can be selected.
DCV calibration adjustments run through 47 steps. At step 45 the DMM range is changed to 100V mode, then back again for 46 && 47.
For DCV && DCI calibration adjustments, after DCV step 47 has finished a pop-up will prompt the user to change the DMM inputs to 'I' and 'LO' and continue with DCI calibration adjustments. The final step is 71.

data.name: Label280.Text
data.value: LOAD will pull saved default counts from system memory to the above && the active area. Pre-Cal will then use these values at Step 3. SAVE will save off values set manually above to system memory. If LOAD not used PDVS2mini values are used.
